│ An LLVM bug in `instcombine` is causing a miscompilation when simplifying a `trunc` of an  │
│ `fshl` intrinsic. The root cause is an incorrect optimization in                           │
│ `SimplifyDemandedUseBits`, which over-aggressively simplifies the operands of `fshl` based │
│ on the bits demanded by the `trunc` user. The logic fails to correctly account for the     │
│ interaction of bits from both operands of `fshl`, leading to an invalid transformation     │
│ that can produce `poison`.                                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ To fix this, I will remove the faulty optimization logic for `fshl` from                   │
│ `SimplifyDemandedUseBits` in                                                               │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSimplifyDemanded.cpp`. This is the safest      │
│ approach to prevent this miscompilation, as a more precise fix would require a             │
│ significantly more complex analysis of the bit interactions within the `fshl` operation.   │
