│ `fshl` intrinsic (`fshl(X, X, C)`). The logic in `SimplifyDemandedUseBits` incorrectly     │
│ simplifies the operand `X` based on the demanded bits, causing the error.                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ My previous attempts were flawed:                                                          │
│ 1.  Disabling the optimization entirely caused regressions.                                │
│ 2.  My proposed replacements for the faulty logic were also incorrect and caused different │
│ regressions.                                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The correct solution is to fix the logic within the `else` block that handles the rotate   │
│ case. The existing code attempts to simplify the operand based on the demanded bits for    │
│ the left-shifted and right-shifted parts separately, which is wrong. When the operand is   │
│ the same, we must consider the combined demanded bits from both shifts before attempting   │
│ any simplification.                                                                        │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will now apply a precise patch that:                                                     │
│ 1.  Calculates the combined mask (`DemandedMaskLHS | DemandedMaskRHS`).                    │
